<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dannig</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Assuming that WIS is not an issue (allready 200+)<P>Forest Loop:<P>2 AC +3 Agi +3 Dex +3 Wis  <P>Ivanyr's Hoop:<P>6 AC +6 Wis +6 Int +6 HP  <P>Is 4 AC and 6 INT worth losing 3 AGI and 3 DEX?<P>Thanks<P>------------------<BR>Dannig   52 Cleric<BR>Dark Elf <BR>Dark Asylum<BR>http://personal.pitnet.net/asylum/<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jaldarith</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It depends on where your agility is.<P>If your agility is sub-100, or gets sub-100 when you remove the forest loop, you want to keep the forest loop.  If you already have 100+ agi and have 3 agi to spare, I would go with the Ivandyr's Hoop, because with the agility bonus, you'd get like 9 or 11 ac instead of 6.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mirriana_00</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, 3 Dex means absolutely nothing unless you are going to melee with a proccing weapon, and even then it would mean something like a .05% increase in proc rates.<P>3 Agi means virtually nothing unless it is going to make you hit 75+ or 100+.  Besides that, I doubt it would end up giving you 4ac.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tailchaser</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Is 4 AC and 6 INT worth losing 3 AGI and 3 DEX?<HR></BLOCKQUOTE>The only situation I can conceive of in which the Forest Loop would be better is if your Agility will drop below 75 by removing it.  Going from 75 to 74 Agility is a <B>huge</B> AC drop; any other Agility modifiers at any other point will have a very very minor effect.  I'd absolutely go for the Ivandyr's Hoop.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Calahad</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">"If your agility is sub-100, or gets sub-100 when you remove the forest loop, you want to keep the forest loop"<P>OK, the paw just put my AGI at 102.  I knew there was penalty for sub-75 AGI, what is the bonus for AGI over 100?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jaldarith</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Agility and Dexterity go in quarters, like 75, 100, 125, etc.  Say for instance you're wearing a Fungi tunic, and you have 99agi with it on, 109 with it off, you're going to be missing a lot of extra AC.<P>If you get a hold of a +1 agi item (like one of those cockatrice feathers....Or is that +cha?), you'll see your AC boost a lot if you hit 100 or above it.<P>Just ask a jeweler to get you a +agi ring or earring or something and compare the AC sub-100 and post-100.  There's also a bonus at 125, but I think that's the last of the bonuses.<P>I don't know the average for bonus over 100, but with my fungi tunic, I have 98 AGI, and I lose like 4 AC when I switch from my Froglok Scale Breastplate.  I have 108 agility with my froggy BP on.  When I put on my Forest Loop instead of my Electrum BS earring, my AC boosts like 12, when I'm wearing my fungi tunic.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
